Description: Epiphone ES 339 Pro -- great guitar for a wide variety of styles. Guitar is very playable and all original equipment but does a nick on the back of the lower bout near the binding, as seen in the photo attached. The label and serial number indicate Dot ES 339, but the official catalog from 2015 doesn't have a Dot ES 339, just a Pro, and the specs for this guitar correspond to the pro, as in the photo included. It has coil-tapping, which puts it in the Pro category, rather than Dot. So, that's a bit odd, but it's a Pro, not Dot. Here's the description of the ES-339 Pro.The semi-hollow Epiphone ES-339 Pro has only been around a short while, but it pays tribute to one of the most well-known guitars in Gibson's line: the ES-335. Its smaller body size makes it more akin to the Gibson ES-339, but the instrument's roots are place firmly in one of the more well-known of Gibson's ES line. The ES-339 Pro is great for a variety of genres, from rock to jazz to country, and is particularly great for players who want a lighter, more movable guitar.
Title: Great playing Epiphone ES-339 Pro,
ConditionDescription: Has a one inch nick in the back next to the binding, as pictured. Otherwise in very good shape with little wear and tear.
